{"title_page": "2000 Halifax Regional Municipality municipal election", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{Orphan|date=March 2017}}\n{{refimprove|date=February 2017}}\n}}\n\nThe 2000 municipal elections of the [[Halifax, Nova Scotia|Halifax]] Regional Municipality in [[Nova Scotia]], [[Canada]], took place on 21 October 2000.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.herald.ns.ca/cgi-bin/home/loadmain?2000/10/21+266.raw|title=X marks the spot: Nova Scotians go to municipal polls|work=The Chronicle Herald|date=21 October 2000|accessdate=24 February 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20001206070000/http://www.herald.ns.ca/cgi-bin/home/loadmain?2000%2F10%2F21+266.raw|archivedate=6 December 2000|url-status=dead}}</ref> Elections have been held every four years since the amalgamation of the cities of Halifax and Dartmouth, the town of Bedford and Halifax County into the Halifax Regional Municipality in 1996. The regional council is made up of twenty three councillors and one mayor, all positions were up for election.\n\nThere are no political parties at the municipal level in Nova Scotia, so all candidates run as independents.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.halifax.ca/election/PastElections/documents/001021cclr.pdf |title=Archived copy |access-date=2017-02-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170301005819/http://www.halifax.ca/election/PastElections/documents/001021cclr.pdf |archive-date=2017-03-01 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==[[Halifax Regional Municipality]] Mayor==\n\n{{Election box begin no party| title=HRM Total Population, 2000 Census: 390,096}}\n{{Election box candidate no party|\n  |candidate  = [[Walter Fitzgerald (politician)|Walter R. Fitzgerald]]\n  |votes      = 000\n  |percentage = 000\n  |change     =\n}}\n{{Election box candidate no party|\n  |candidate  = [[Peter J. Kelly]]\n  |votes      = 00\n  |percentage = 00\n  |change     =\n}}\n{{Election box candidate no party|\n  |candidate  = Ken Ozmon\n  |votes      = 00\n  |percentage = 00\n  |change 