{"title_page": "Bill Horne", "text_new": "{{Infobox officeholder\n| honorific-prefix    = \n| image = <!-- only free-content images are allowed for depicting living people - see [[WP:NONFREE]] --> |\n| name = Bill Horne\n| caption =\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1948|3|28}}\n| birth_place = \n| honorific-suffix= [[Nova Scotia House of Assembly|MLA]]\n| assembly        = Nova Scotia House of\n| constituency_AM =[[Waverley-Fall River-Beaver Bank]]\n| term_start = October 8, 2013\n| term_end = \n| predecessor = [[Percy Paris]]\n| successor = \n| party = [[Nova Scotia Liberal Party|Liberal]]  \n| religion = \n| spouse = \n| occupation = }}\n\n'''Bill Horne''' (born March 28, 1948) is a [[Canadians|Canadian]] politician. He who was elected to the [[Nova Scotia House of Assembly]] in the [[2013 Nova Scotia general election|2013 provincial election]]. A member of the [[Nova Scotia Liberal Party]], he represents the electoral district of [[Waverley-Fall River-Beaver Bank]].<ref>[http://metronews.ca/news/halifax/818290/nova-scotia-votes-riding-by-riding-results-for-halifax-region/ \"Nova Scotia votes: Riding-by-riding results for Halifax region\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140228045416/http://metronews.ca/news/halifax/818290/nova-scotia-votes-riding-by-riding-results-for-halifax-region/ |date=2014-02-28 }}. ''[[Metro International|Metro]]'', October 8, 2013.</ref>\n\nHorne graduated from [[Saint Mary's University (Halifax)|Saint Mary's University]] in 1972 with a Bachelor of Science.<ref>[https://www.smu.ca/about/news/2013/provincial-election-results.html Eight Saint Mary's Alumni Headed to Province House]{{Dead link|date=June 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} Saint Mary's University</ref>\n\n==Electoral record==\n{{Election box begin | title=[[2013 Nova Scotia general election]]}}\n|-\n{{Canadian_politics/party_colours/Liberal/row}} \n|[[Nova Scotia Liberal Party|Liberal]]\n|Bill Horne\n|align=\"right\"|3,588\n|align=\"right\"|43